{"TopicId":209924,"ForumId":112,"TopicTitle":"Kerbals with adjustable jumping strength","CreatedByName":"jclovis3","CreatedById":188635,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-28T04:07:41Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"jclovis3","CreatedById":188635,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-28T04:07:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAllow Kerbals to reduce the force of their jumps on low gravity planets if they wanted to. I mean, it\u0027s cool to jump over the entire ship, but when you have to leave your EVA pack behind to carry a science kit to place, your only way back in is a well aimed jump or an inflatable airlock placed down low to the ground on a girder or robotic part.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"intelliCom","CreatedById":209738,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-28T04:10:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224179820\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209924\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221664338061\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022188635\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022jclovis3\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, jclovis3 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAllow Kerbals to reduce the force of their jumps on low gravity planets if they wanted to. I mean, it\u0027s cool to jump over the entire ship, but when you have to leave your EVA pack behind to carry a science kit to place, your only way back in is a well aimed jump or an inflatable airlock placed down low to the ground on a girder or robotic part.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d say this could be implemented by holding space to determine jumping height, which can be toggled in settings of course in exchange for the original \u0022m